<h1>Calculator to work out Days, Hours, Minutes, Seconds using Sec as input=
</h1>

<p>The purpose of this page is to allow you to calculator the number of Day=
s, Hours, Minutes, Seconds,=20
starting with a large number of seconds.</p>

<h2>Seconds to days:</h2>

<p>Enter the number of seconds in the light grey box below (by modifying th=
e default value shown) and then click the calculate button to obtain result=
s in the green boxes.</p>

<form action=3D"https://www.satsig.net/training/seconds-days-hours-minutes-=
calculator.htm#">
      <table style=3D"border: 1px; padding: 3px; border-collapse: collapse;=
 width: 317px; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;">
        <tbody><tr>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #dedede; text-align: center; width=
: 200px">
          <p><b>Input Total Seconds:</b></p></td>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #dedede; width: 168px">
          <label><input size=3D"8" value=3D"1234567" name=3D"totalseconds">=
<b>s</b></label></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 200px"><b>Days</b>=
</td>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 168px">
          <label><input name=3D"daysout" size=3D"10"><b>d</b></label></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 200px"><b>Hours</b=
></td>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 168px">
          <label><input name=3D"hoursout" size=3D"10"><b>h</b></label></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 200px"><b>Minutes<=
/b></td>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 168px">
          <label><input name=3D"minutesout" size=3D"10"><b>m</b></label></t=
d>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 200px"><b>Seconds<=
/b></td>
          <td style=3D"background-color: #99ff99; width: 168px">
          <label><input name=3D"secondsout" size=3D"10"><b>s</b></label></t=
d>
        </tr>
      </tbody></table>
      <p style=3D"text-align: center"><input type=3D"button" value=3D"Click=
 to calculate results"></p>
</form>

<p>If you want to know how this  calculator works have a look at the html a=
nd javascript code which is embedded in the text html code of this page. Do=
 something like=20
this: "Right mouse click on this page", then do "View Page Source". The jav=
ascript code is also shown below:</p>

<p style=3D"font-family: Courier New">function computeform(form) {<br>
<br>
var totalseconds;<br>
<br>
var day =3D 86400;<br>
var hour =3D 3600;<br>
var minute =3D 60;<br>
<br>
var totalseconds =3D form.totalseconds.value;</p>
<p style=3D"font-family: Courier New">var daysout =3D Math.floor(totalsecon=
ds / day);<br>
var hoursout =3D Math.floor((totalseconds - daysout * day)/hour);<br>
var minutesout =3D Math.floor((totalseconds - daysout * day - hoursout * ho=
ur)/minute);<br>
var secondsout =3D totalseconds - daysout * day - hoursout * hour - minutes=
out * minute;<br>
<br>
form.daysout.value =3D daysout;<br>
form.hoursout.value =3D hoursout;<br>
form.minutesout.value =3D minutesout;<br>
form.secondsout.value =3D secondsout;<br>
return;<br>
}<br>
</p>

<p>Have fun and good luck.&nbsp;&nbsp; I thought about including a 'year' o=
utput=20
and wondered how long was a year. Maybe 365.2422 days, but I thought that t=
hat=20
might confuse people.&nbsp; </p>

<h2>How many seconds in a day:</h2>

<p>One day has been set equal to 86400 seconds exactly. Note that a siderea=
l day=20
is 23 hours 56 minutes 4.091 seconds, which is the sidereal average. Read m=
ore=20
about <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidereal_time" target=3D"_bl=
ank">sidereal time</a> on=20
Wikipedia</p>

<p>If you would like&nbsp; to make a calculator page yourself, try copying =
this=20
page and then editing the source html code to suit whatever you want. Delet=
e the=20
12 lines near at the bottom, between the two <b>&lt;hr&gt;</b> elements, wh=
ich makes=20
an advert appear.</p>

